==English==

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|hondfast}}, past participle of {{inh|en|enm|hondfesten||to betroth}}, from {{etyl|non|en}} {{m|non|handfesta||to strike a bargain, pledge}}, itself from {{m|non|hönd||hand}} + {{m|non|festa||to fasten, fix, affirm}} (compare see [[past-]] in Indo-European roots).

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[hold]], grasp; [[custody]], power of confining or keeping.
#*{{RQ:Shakespeare Cymbeline|act=I|scene=v|passage=And the remembrancer of her to hold<br>The '''hand-fast''' to her lord. I have given him that}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[contract]], agreement, covenant; specifically [[betrothal]], [[espousal]].

